---
layout: foundation.njk
permalink: 'index.html'
theme:
  color: "#d22d6f"
  fonts: ["Roboto", "Lato", "Helvetica Neue"]
tagline_short: "specialized skills for AI coding agents"
tagline: "Specialized agent skills that streamline common developer workflows and reduce token usage."
---

{% css %}{% include "./styles.css" %}{% endcss %}
{% from "skill-chips.njk" import skillChips %}

<header class="container hero">
	<p class="eyebrow chip">Skills for AI agents</p>
	{# Keep the package name on the dashes (non-breaking hyphen U+2011) and let it
	   wrap only after the slash (<wbr>), so it breaks as "@allons-y/ | agent-skills". #}
	<h1>{{ title | default(site.title) | replace("-", "&#8209;") | replace("/", "/<wbr>") | safe }}</h1>
	<p class="lede">{{ tagline }}</p>
	<p class="btn-group">
		<a class="btn primary" href="#install">Get started</a>
		<a class="btn" href="{{ site.repo.url }}"><span class="fa-brands fa-github" aria-hidden="true"></span> View on GitHub</a>
	</p>
	{% include "trust-strip.njk" %}
	<div class="hero-terminal">
		<span class="terminal-bar" aria-hidden="true"><i></i><i></i><i></i></span>
		{% highlight "shell" %}/plugin marketplace add {{ site.repo.slug }}
/plugin install {{ site.featured.name }}@{{ site.marketplace_name }}{% endhighlight %}
	</div>
</header>

<main id="main" class="container">
	<section id="what" aria-labelledby="what-heading" class="layout grid">
		<div class="content">
			<h2 id="what-heading">
				What is an agent skill?
				<a class="anchor" href="#what" aria-label="Permalink to What is this?">#</a>
			</h2>
			<p>
				<strong>Agent skills</strong> are focused, self-contained capability
				packs you can drop into an AI coding agent. Each skill bundles a
				<code>SKILL.md</code> (the prompt and trigger description), a
				Node.js implementation (where applicable), and a robust test suite — all under one directory.
			</p>
			<p>
				Claude Code installs them natively via the plugin marketplace. Other
				agent harnesses — Cursor, OpenCode, Aider, or anything built on the
				Claude Agent SDK — can vendor any skill directory with one
				<code>npx</code> command. No vendor lock-in.
			</p>
		</div>

		{% if site.featured -%}
		<a class="card featured" href="{{ site.featured.detailUrl }}">
			<header>
				<h2 class="chip">Featured skill</h2>
				<h3 id="featured-skill">{{ site.featured.name }}</h3>
				{{ skillChips(site.featured) }}
			</header>
			<div class="body">
				<p>{{ site.featured.description }}</p>
			</div>
			<div class="footer">
				<p class="cta">Read the docs</p>
			</div>
		</a>
		{%- endif %}
	</section>

	<section id="trust" aria-labelledby="trust-heading" class="layout stacked">
		<header>
			<h2 id="trust-heading">
				Built to be trusted
				<a class="anchor" href="#trust" aria-label="Permalink to Built to be trusted">#</a>
			</h2>
			<p>These aren't prompt snippets pasted from a gist. Every skill is engineered, tested, and maintained like production software.</p>
		</header>
		<div class="layout grid quality-grid">
			{% for item in site.quality -%}
			<article class="quality">
				<span class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><span class="{{ item.icon }} fa-xl"></span></span>
				<h3>{{ item.title }}</h3>
				<p>{{ item.text | safe }}</p>
			</article>
			{%- endfor %}
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="skills" aria-labelledby="skills-heading" class="layout stacked">
		<header>
			<h2 id="skills-heading">
				Available skills
				<a class="anchor" href="#skills" aria-label="Permalink to Available skills">#</a>
			</h2>
			<p>All skills currently published in this marketplace.</p>
		</header>
		<article class="layout grid">
			{% for skill in site.skills -%}
			<a class="card" href="{{ skill.detailUrl }}">
				<div class="header">
					<h3>{{ skill.name }}</h3>
					{{ skillChips(skill) }}
				</div>
				<div class="body">
					<p>{{ skill.description | truncate(220) }}</p>
				</div>
				<div class="footer layout stacked">
					{% if skill.commands.length > 0 -%}
					<p class="meta">
						<span class="label">Commands:</span>
						{% for command in skill.commands %}<code>{{ command }}</code>{% if not loop.last %} {% endif %}{% endfor %}
					</p>
					{%- endif %}
					{% if skill.triggers.length > 0 -%}
					<p class="meta">
						<span class="label">Triggers: </span>
						{% for trigger in skill.triggers %}<code>"{{ trigger }}"</code>{% if not loop.last %} {% endif %}{% endfor %}
					</p>
					{%- endif %}
					<p class="cta">Learn more</p>
				</div>
			</a>
			{%- endfor %}
		</article>
	</section>

	<section id="install" aria-labelledby="install-heading" class="layout stacked">
		<header>
			<h2 id="install-heading">
				Install
				<a class="anchor" href="#install" aria-label="Permalink to Install">#</a>
			</h2>
			<p>Pick the card for your agent harness. Every install uses the same skill payload — there's no Claude-specific wiring inside <code>SKILL.md</code>.</p>
		</header>
		<div class="layout grid">
			{% for harness in site.harnesses -%}
			<article class="card{% if harness.recommended %} featured{% endif %}" id="install-{{ harness.id }}">
				<header>
					{% if harness.recommended %}<p class="chip">Recommended</p>{% endif %}
					<h3>
						<span class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><span class="{{ harness.icon }} fa-xl"></span></span>
						{{- harness.name }}
					</h3>
				</header>
				<div class="body">
					<h3>{{ harness.tagline }}</h3>
					<p>{{ harness.description | safe }}</p>
				</div>
				<footer>
					{% highlight "shell" %}{% for command in harness.commands %}{{ command | safe }}{% if not loop.last %}
{% endif %}{% endfor %}{% endhighlight %}
				</footer>
			</article>
			{%- endfor %}
		</div>
		<p class="note">
			For Node-runtime skills with dependencies, run
			<code>npm install</code> in the vendored directory once.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section id="programmatic" aria-labelledby="programmatic-heading" class="layout stacked">
		<header>
			<h2 id="programmatic-heading">
				Programmatic usage
				<a class="anchor" href="#programmatic" aria-label="Permalink to Programmatic usage">#</a>
			</h2>
			<p>Tool builders can enumerate skills dynamically via the exported <code>getSkills()</code> helper.</p>
		</header>
{% highlight "js" %}
import { getSkills } from "{{ site.package.name }}";

const skills = getSkills();
// returns =>
// [
//   {
//     name: "{{ site.featured.name }}",
//     path: "/path/to/skills/{{ site.featured.name }}",
//     description: "{{ site.featured.description | truncate(50) }}",
//     mdPath: "/path/to/skills/{{ site.featured.name }}/SKILL.md",
//   },
//   ...
// ]
{% endhighlight %}
	</section>

	<section id="contributing" aria-labelledby="contributing-heading" class="layout stacked">
		<header>
			<h2 id="contributing-heading">
				Contributing
				<a class="anchor" href="#contributing" aria-label="Permalink to Contributing">#</a>
			</h2>
		</header>
		<div class="content">
			<p>
				New skills, improvements, bug fixes, and documentation are all welcome.
				See <a href="{{ site.repo.url }}/blob/main/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>
				for environment setup, the test/lint/eval workflow, and the PR
				checklist.
			</p>
			<p>Some ideas if you're looking for a starting point:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>GitHub PR review summarizer</li>
				<li>Linear / Jira issue triage</li>
				<li>Slack digest summarizer</li>
				<li>Daily standup generator from git log</li>
				<li>Accessibility audit runner (pairs nicely with <code>design-system</code>)</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</main>

{% footer %}
<div>
	<p class="title">Resources</p>
	<ul>
		<li><a href="{{ site.repo.url }}"><span class="fa-brands fa-github" aria-hidden="true"></span> GitHub</a></li>
		<li><a href="{{ site.npm.url }}"><span class="fa-brands fa-npm" aria-hidden="true"></span> npm</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>
<div>
	<p class="title">Resources</p>
	<ul>
		<li><a href="{{ site.bugs.url }}">Report an issue</a></li>
		<li><a href="{{ site.repo.url }}/blob/main/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md">Contributing guide</a></li>
	</ul>
</div>
{% endfooter %}
